Book Synopsis
This book, full of actual examples, aims to bring to life all of the dynamic, subtlety, and variety of business strategy as it is practiced in the
real world and in real companies. The author does not purport to be inventing strategy in this book or to be revealing the secrets of
Japanese business and strategic planning. Rather, he is exploring with the reader the ways in which the strategist must think, the key
principles and thought patterns that real-world strategists have used to move their companies forward in Japan and throughout the world.
He explores the relationship of the Strategic Triangle formed by the company, the customer, and the competition and shows how these
factors must be the basis for all strategic thinking and planning.
